  "texts": [
    "See [20][21][22] for more on the relationship between vulnerability, agency, and plasticity.",
    "6 This idea is also discussed with respect to intelligence and uncertainty in [25], with specific ideas around phase codes and tensors as the mechanisms.",
    "There are other candidates for such over-arching concepts, including resolution of ambiguity [26] and free energy minimization [27][28][29].",
    "7 This maintenance requires constant adjustment of the estimated boundary between Self and world, and of the sensors and effectors an agent thinks it has.",
    "The plasticity of this process, and lack of allegiance to evolutionary priors, is revealed when humans, with millions of years of history as a tetrapod, adopt a new limb as their own within minutes of experience in the \"rubber hand illusion\" experiments and other cases of sensorymotor augmentation [30][31][32][33], or in syndromes where patients deny that their conventional bodyparts belong to them [34]."
